eft-wingism, which they blamed on my mother. I think they both aided and abetted each other, but she was blamed for that!  So we didn\rquote t really get to know that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1276273  side of the family very much.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1852626\charrsid1852626 On my mother\rquote s side, I didn\rquote 
t know my maternal gr
andfather, he died, rather unhappily. He was actually more or less mashed down by the Black and Tans, who were the special police - kind of oppressive police in Northern Ireland, which again, my mother has never forgotten.  He survived it, but never was r
ight after that.  I do just remember my maternal grandmother \endash  Granny \endash 
