o 100 per cent, and slightly less literal minded, is very much in that. [He] lives in Lisburn, just outside Belfast, now, with many children of his own.  He and I used to fight like anything, as children.  Well, I was the oldest, and I was always being pu
t in charge of these two younger brothers, Diarmid and David, and I hated it, because they would not do what I said, and yet they were supposed to!  But Diarmid and I get on so well now, we would su}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
