\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1852626\charrsid1852626 Ruth:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1852626\charrsid1852626 
It depended where you were coming from.  The functionalist anthropology, which was not the only thing, but was very powerful in British anthropology at that time \endash  yes, well, if people said things and it had a narrative form, it wouldn\rquote 
t really be interesting to a functionalist anthropologist because what you\rquote re interested in was how the social order stuck together and was maintained, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
