78 David and I were invited to go off, first of all for two years, to the University of the South Pacific in Fiji, which was a university which had come to serve all the English-speaking islands, small islands, in 
the South Pacific: Samoa, the Gilbert Islands, as they were then called, the Ellis Islands, the New Hebrides, and many many others. Because all these island populations were very small, they didn\rquote 
t have a big enough population in their Civil Service, for example, to send people off for three full years to Suva full-time campus - Suva being the capital of Fiji \endash 
 so the university there was very much beginning to expand on distance education, so that people could study at a distance, say, for two years, in Sa
moa or somewhere, and in the third year, come and top up.  And so we went out partly to use our Open University experience to help to do that, as well as teaching on campus.  It was the most wonderful three years - but I won\rquote t go on about that!

