of. The commitment of it very much went to our hearts, we really really wanted to be part of that, though we had actually intended not to come back for one more year.  We couldn\rquote 
t leave Nigeria until I think July, and our jobs were beginning in September. Well, I think I said I wouldn\rquote t begin till October, but David the beginning of September, so we couldn\rquote 
t come back to house-hunt in that time. But wonderfully, David\rquote s parents were living in Northampton, not very far away, and we looked through the brochure
s, and then she went and looked at the houses and she, after a lot of telegramming, and turning others down, she found this house, which is just lovely!  Just right for us.  In Bletchley, with a big garden. Well, it\rquote 
s now a bit too big, but David loves gardening, and he\rquote s so good at it. Near the local schools, ten minutes, 12, 15 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4147989\charrsid1852626 minutes\rquote  walk}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1852626\charrsid1852626  from the station, very close to the Open University, ten }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4147989\charrsid1852626 minutes\rquote  drive}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1852626\charrsid1852626  or something. We\rquote ve been very happy there.  I
\rquote m very glad we went there, because a lot of our colleagues joining the Open University at that time, when Milton Keynes was just kind of starting up, said they couldn\rquote 
t possibly come and live in that place, a cultural desert, and they wanted to stay in Oxford or Cambridge, or Brighton or Bristol or Edinburgh, I think, in one case in London, in cultured places. There wasn\rquote 
t a residence qualification at that time, partly because Milton Keynes was just growing up. It was a mistake, actually, I think, that they didn\rquote t.  But we wanted to live close by, because with three small children and two jobs, we weren\rquote 
t going to have time to commute, and we didn\rquote t want to go and live in a romantic village somewhere where there wouldn\rquote t be services that we could quickly access, so we actually, I think, made absolutely th
e right choice, and we kept the house when we went to Fiji, and we\rquote re still there.  It\rquote s very nice.  A nice leafy part of Bletchley.
